Ok, now I finally understand. I got confused when I read "rows selected" which I took to mean each row had a checkbox to select it.

Anyway, to achieve what is required, set the pager `savePages` option, then ignore the set page number on initialization ([demo](http://jsfiddle.net/Mottie/yfwwzvL8/321/)):

```js
$(function() {
  $('table')
    .on('pagerBeforeInitialized', function() {
      // this always resets to the first page on initialization
    	this.config.pager.page = 0;
    })
    .tablesorter({
      theme: 'blue',
      widthFixed: false,
      widgets: ['zebra', 'pager'],
      widgetOption: {
      	pager_savePages: true
      }
    });
});
```

