Hi Chris,

the problem was, that I missed the handling of intervals in time expressions.
In particular, the expression 'night' from your input letter would throw the error since instead of a simple entry for 'value' in 'value', Duckling returns two dicts for 'from' and 'to':

```
{
    :dim :time,
    :body "night",
    :value {
        :type "interval",
        :from {
            :value "2016-10-17T18:00:00.000+01:00",
            :grain :hour
        },
        :to {
            :value "2016-10-18T00:00:00.000+01:00",
            :grain :hour
        },
        :values (
            {
                :type "interval",
                :from {
                    :value "2016-10-17T18:00:00.000+01:00",
                    :grain :hour
                },
                :to {
                    :value "2016-10-18T00:00:00.000+01:00",
                    :grain :hour
                }
            }{
                :type "interval",
                :from {
                    :value "2016-10-18T18:00:00.000+01:00",
                    :grain :hour
                },
                :to {
                    :value "2016-10-19T00:00:00.000+01:00",
                    :grain :hour
                }
            }{
                :type "interval",
                :from {
                    :value "2016-10-19T18:00:00.000+01:00",
                    :grain :hour
                },
                :to {
                    :value "2016-10-20T00:00:00.000+01:00",
                    :grain :hour
                }
            }
        )
    },
    :start 478,
    :end 483,
    :latent true
}
```

It should be fixed now and I just pushed the latest version (v.1.1.3) to pypi 😋

