The Apache plugin lists itself as misconfigured if it believes there is a problem with your server configuration. It's important to note that the Apache plugin does not currently work on all Apache setups. If our plugin cannot understand your config, it will list itself as misconfigured and it will almost certainly not work.

@kroeckx, is it possible the Apache plugin listed itself as misconfigured before you ran it? The subtleties of what I just described are not at all made clear to the user so it seems perfectly reasonable that you would have done so.

If this is the case, this suggests we should bump the priority of #990 into the "1.0 for launch" (I just did) and close this issue. If Apache can't parse your config, it is reasonable to expect it won't edit it properly

